**Note:** Copy this `loading.tsx` file to any route segment that needs its own loading state. Next.js will automatically show this component while the page content is loading.

#### `src/app/robots.ts` - SEO Robots Configuration

```typescript
import { MetadataRoute } from "next";

export default function robots(): MetadataRoute.Robots {
  const baseUrl = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL || "https://example.com";

  return {
    rules: [
      {
        userAgent: "*",
        allow: "/",
        disallow: ["/api/", "/admin/"],
      },
    ],
    sitemap: `${baseUrl}/sitemap.xml`,
  };
}
```

**Note:** Update the `disallow` array with any routes you want to exclude from search engine indexing. Add a `sitemap.ts` file when you're ready to generate a sitemap.

