#### Environment File Guidelines

1. **`.env.local`** - Local development secrets (NEVER commit)
2. **`.env.example`** - Template with placeholder values (commit this)
3. **`.env.production`** - Production values set in deployment platform

**Important Rules:**

- Never commit actual API keys or secrets
- Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix only for values safe to expose to browsers
- Server-only secrets should NOT have the `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix
- Document all required environment variables in `.env.example`

